  "description": "Harry Ludvig Johansson was a Swedish lecturer who was born in Uppsala in 1907. He obtained his Bachelor's degree, Master's degree, and Licentiate degree from Uppsala University before earning his Doctoral degree in 1942. He focused his research on the scattering of radiation by hydrogen-like atoms. He served as a substitute teacher, part-time teacher, and assistant professor at Uppsala University and as a lecturer in Mathematics and Mechanics at Norrköping Technical Gymnasium. Harry Ludvig married Maj Ternsitedt in 1938 and they had one child, Karin, in 1944."
